# Docker-only workflow for PHP/Composer

This project has **no local PHP or Composer** in the host (e.g. WSL). All PHP and Composer commands **must** run inside the dev container.

## Do not run

- `composer ...` on the host
- `php ...` on the host
- `vendor/bin/phpunit ...` on the host

These will fail; use the Docker workflow below instead.

## Correct commands

**Start dev containers (once):**
```bash
make up-dev
```

**Install dependencies:**
```bash
make install
```

**Run tests:**
```bash
docker compose -f .docker/docker-compose.yml -f .docker/docker-compose.dev.yml exec -u 1000:1000 app composer test
```

**Run PHPStan:**
```bash
docker compose -f .docker/docker-compose.yml -f .docker/docker-compose.dev.yml exec -u 1000:1000 app composer check:phpstan
```

**Run coverage (HTML):**
```bash
docker compose -f .docker/docker-compose.yml -f .docker/docker-compose.dev.yml exec -u 1000:1000 app composer test:coverage
```

**Single test class or filter:**
```bash
docker compose -f .docker/docker-compose.yml -f .docker/docker-compose.dev.yml exec -u 1000:1000 app vendor/bin/phpunit --filter SomeTest
```

